  "metadata": {
    "name": "Disable Prelinking",
    "description": "The prelinking feature changes binaries in an attempt to decrease their startup\ntime. In order to disable it, change or add the following line inside the file\n<tt>/etc/sysconfig/prelink</tt>:\n<pre>PRELINKING=no</pre>\nNext, run the following command to return binaries to a normal, non-prelinked state:\n<pre>$ sudo /usr/sbin/prelink -ua</pre>",
    "rationale": "Because the prelinking feature changes binaries, it can interfere with the\noperation of certain software and/or modes such as AIDE, FIPS, etc.",
